@startuml fig-A07-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title SDN Learning Switch — E2 Flow (Flood → Learn → Unicast → Age)

participant "h1\nport 1" as H1 #FFE0B2
participant "s1\n(OVS)" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "Controller" as C #E1BEE7
participant "h2\nport 2" as H2 #FFE0B2
participant "h3\nport 3" as H3 #FFE0B2

== PHASE 1 — UNKNOWN DESTINATION (flood) ==

H1 -> SW : ARP Request: who has h2?\n(src MAC aa:aa)
SW -> C : packet-in (unknown dst ff:ff)
C -> C : learn: aa:aa → port 1
C -> SW : flood ARP to all ports
SW -> H2 : ARP Request (broadcast)
SW -> H3 : ARP Request (broadcast)
note right of C : R3: arp || icmp || ip >= 5

== PHASE 2 — LEARNING AND RULE INSTALL ==

H2 -> SW : ARP Reply (src MAC bb:bb)
SW -> C : packet-in
C -> C : learn: bb:bb → port 2
C -> SW : flow-mod: dst=aa:aa → port 1\n(idle_timeout=60)
C -> SW : flow-mod: dst=bb:bb → port 2\n(idle_timeout=60)
SW -> H1 : ARP Reply (unicast via rule)
note right of C : R1: tcp.port==6653 >= 1\nR2: tcp.port==6653 && tcp.len>0 >= 5

== PHASE 3 — UNICAST (no controller involvement) ==

H1 -[#43A047]> SW : ICMP Echo → h2
SW -[#43A047]> H2 : forwarded by flow rule\n(no packet-in)
H2 -[#43A047]-> SW : ICMP Reply → h1
SW -[#43A047]-> H1 : forwarded by flow rule
note right of SW #E8F5E9 : controller not involved

== PHASE 4 — AGEING ==

... idle_timeout expires (60 s) ...
SW -> SW : flow entry removed
H1 -> SW : ICMP Echo → h2
SW -> C : packet-in (rule expired)
C -> C : re-learn, reinstall rule
note right of C : ageing demonstrated

legend right
  Transition: flood → unicast is observable
  in PCAP (broadcast ARP then direct ICMP).
  dump-flows confirms installed rules and
  their removal after idle timeout expiry.
endlegend
@enduml
